place_description: We may not be a big fancy coffee house but we have a lot of love and compassion for our customers and community. Alice Jules coffeehouse “Where the coffee is brewed especially for YOU”

reviews_data.review_text: I so love this coffee shop even with all the coffee business coming to monroe. This coffee shop is still the best and my favorite . I've never gotten bad coffee or matcha from here. ps try the bagel bomb  u want me disappointed.
Jordan and Andrea helped me pick the best drink! I love this place! I will tell everyone I know to come here!!!!
We had the best coffee today! The ladies were so kind and helpful, the chocolate chip & apple scones are delicious. It's a super cute place with indoor and outdoor seating.. I'm so glad we stopped!
Alice Jules has the best coffee, morning treats and staff.  Kent and his team work so hard to make sure you have an enjoyable experience. Highly recommend!
Best coffee and service in town!  We love Kent and his team!
Always a smiling face to serve you.  Great coffee and pastries!  The icon of coffee houses.

It's one thing to serve great coffee, but it's another to serve the community with just as much passion-- and that's exactly what Kent and Melody do everyday. Beyond brewing exceptional coffee, they have built a space where kindness, generosity, and support for local initiatives thrive.
Highly recommend stopping by-- not just for the delicious drinks, but for the heartwarming atmosphere.
Thankyou for supporting The Flowerbasket.
In the immortal words of Yogi Berra... "Nobody goes there anymore, it's too crowded"
Good luck finding parking. And if there is more than a couple people inline might as well just go home and brew your own.
Great cozy, homey and friendly place. We will definitely go back.
Great place. Friendly staff and tasty coffee!
Quaint coffee shop in downtown Monroe. Lovely seasonal coffee and treat selections. Some local gifts as well. Plenty of indoor and outdoor seating.
Best coffee shop in town!  Great coffee with an awesome atmosphere. And super friendly staff!
Great coffee and a wonderful staff!
A friendly, cozy place for a coffee date!
Not only is this the best coffee around and best chai also the best service. People are always so kind and helpful and whoever has been choosing the music lately has been KILLING it!!
Love the local coffee shop. They have a huge variety of flavors and coffee. A must have if in the Monroe area
Great service, great staff and excellent products. Outstanding community support and partnership
We had Alice Jules cater our event today with coffee & tea . It was fabulous.  Lots of compliments on the coffee.  We definitely recommend them !  Wonderful folks & service was top notch
i absolutely love going to alice jules. the staff always greets you with a big smile and is always so friendly. they get their drinks out so quickly and it tastes do amazing!!!

One of the most quaint little coffee shops in town. The staff/owners are so welcoming and pleasant. They are very community minded and are always holding events for families to spend time together. A wonderful place to come whether it's to catch up with friends, or spend a little alone time reading a book. It never disappoints.
The people are warm and welcoming. The coffee, tea, smoothies and Chilly Alice are amazing. Won't go anywhere else.

First time there they served me daily special which was a decaf coffee with chocolate and caramel nut notes. So good! It's not easy to find decaf on tap in most coffee shops,  usually have to get an espresso drink. Was so pleased they had decaf and even flavored! The banana nut muffin was great and the atmosphere was its own experience! Highly recommend!!!

Such a sweet and quaint coffee shop right in the heart of historic Monroe. Coffee is delicious and the service is top notch. A great place to sip your favorite coffee with a tasty pastry. A must visit!
Always my go too place for a pick-me-up. Coffee is always good, and the staff is always kind.

I was in the area and I stumbled across this charming and amazing coffee shop! I like trying new flavors of lattes that I have not tried before so I asked the barista about her recommendations. Makenna was phenomenal! She asked me about my preferences and she provided several, too hard to choose from, recommendations! She whipped up the Nutty Irishman for me and it was perfect! Such a cute, quaint and cozy atmosphere along with wonderful service! What more can a coffee lover as for?!?

We have been going to Alice Jules for years. Amazing coffee and Lattes, but you know what keeps us coming back. The people and service we receive! There are a lot of coffee shops in Monroe but none of them have this type of customer service. Thank you Alice Jules for providing a great product with the BEST service. Highly recommend Alice Jules!!
This place rocks!

I absolutely love this coffee shop. It was my favorite to get every morning before school-it actually made me want to get up out of bed. The owners and every single person on staff is kind and would go out of their way to help you if you needed it.

Alice Jules is one of my favorite spots to grab coffee and the occasional treat! The staff is so friendly each time you go in. It is very obvious that they care for each and every one of their customers! You leave feeling like family. They offer lots of treats from local bakers that pair great with your coffee!
Place is amazing with amazing people working there !!
This is best place to go, have coffee, relax and unwind. The team at Alice Jules is wonderful.
Amazing coffee, eats, service and atmosphere! You're genuinely treated like family from start to finish.

This is a great place for any type of coffee. Everyone is super friendly and they all make you feel welcomed. Best place in town to get coffee and pastries. Great place to sit with loved ones and enjoy a drink of your choice.

Alice Jules  is a gem for anyone who appreciates great coffee in a welcoming atmosphere. The moment you step in, the inviting aroma of freshly brewed coffee sets the tone for a fantastic experience. The menu has something for everyone. There's plenty of seating, making it a great spot for working, catching up with friends, or simply enjoying a quiet moment. The staff is incredibly friendly and knowledgeable, always happy to recommend drinks. Whether you're looking for your daily caffeine fix or a place to spend a leisurely afternoon, Alice Jules delivers every time. Highly recommended!
Warm friendly atmosphere. Knowledgeable staff. Great coffee!! Well known in the community for service and quality. Did I mention the amazing coffee!?
The coffee is top notch and the customer service is great. I always feel like family at Alice Jules.  We try to always make a stop to get the best cup of coffee in Monroe!
Alice Jules is my favorite coffee shop!! Everyone is so kind and welcoming.
Great coffee from great people! Stop by this adorable little place, you won't regret it

Don't waste your time visit this place.
Don't understand why they call coffee house if barista don't know how to do light roast coffee.
Substance is what they make taste awful, truckstop, coffee most of the time much better.  So coffee quality not even gas station level.

alice jules is by far my favorite coffee house in town. the atmosphere is so welcoming and friendly and everyone who works here is extremely attentive and kind. Michelle and Kent are my favorite employees and go above and beyond for customers , and the coffee is delicious! try the oreo chilly alice it's YUM

Alice Jules is more than just a coffee shop. It's got great coffee, yes, and it's in a charming historic home, but the real value is in the staff. Everyone is friendly and will take a minute to chat and get to know you if it's not busy. The owner always has a joke or some quick wit, while the baristas are friendly and polite. I'm a fan of their lattes (the snickerdoodle is delicious!), but they've also got a good selection of pastries, scones, and a variety of non-coffee offerings such as their wonderful chai teas and smoothies.
Alice Jules excellent coffee and delightful staff have become part of my routine, and I can't imagine being without either.

P.S: Mechele has excellent advice.

Fantastic gem in Monroe.  The owner and staff are friendly and give personalized attention to their customers.  The drinks are top notch.  Wonderful atmosphere to hang out with friends. Highly recommend.
Amazing owners!!! Let us in on a day they were closed. So nice and great coffee!!!
Wonderful coffee house with the most friendly staff!

Great customer service!  I stopped today to get a cup of coffee. I start by saying I am not an avid coffee drinker. I let them know this and they made a suggestion, I did not like it. Before I left the establishment they made sure that I had a perfect cup of coffee that I enjoyed at no charge.  If you haven't tried them you should go.  #MonroeGem
Local and lovely place to patronize!
Great coffee and desserts. Friendly service. Fun place to sit and relax.
coffee is always good and their matcha is delicious

Best coffee shop in the Carolinas. Superior brews, phenomenal quality, hand made/created local products, knowledgeable & kind staff, and owners who truly understand the meaning of being present to and for your community.
Great place to catch up with friends and get a cup of tea. Lillie welcomed me and took my order swiftly. May the reader of this Review have a very Rad day!
Amazing specialty lattes and smoothies! Great place to catch up with a friend :)

Alice Jules is a favorite spot. The atmosphere is cozy and comfortable. The owner and staff are so friendly and provide excellent service. Their coffee is very good. Whether you sit on the porch or inside, it's a great place to come and enjoy coffee, read, talk, just be.

What a great coffeehouse! Such a neat space and lovely staff. I'd had a long day, with a less than awesome earlier tea latte from another coffeeshop, but my ice London Fog was great! Customized to my liking and a couple of red velvet cake pops to take home for dessert 

Parking was a little tight and I'm not sure if they had wheelchair access.

Alice Jules is your neighborhood coffee house! Its a place to not only get great coffee and pastry, but your welcomed and served like a family member! The Victorian house turned to coffee house and gives that a feeling of home..and you don't want to leave! I have been going here for over 12  years! They are also one of the few coffee houses that serves fresh roasted flavored coffees with out the syrups to flavor..It is so fun to get coffee flavors of the season! .. I could go on  and on but if you haven't gone here yet..get going!!!  You will become a regular I promise!
I've been here a few times with my wife, and it's always been delightful! There's a wide variety of drinks and pastries available, and the staff is very charming and kind.
The most perfect coffee house ever! Such a comfortable vibe and the owner is amazing!!

Walking into Alice Jules feels like coming home. The staff are friendly and always greet me with a smile and the owner is always there (which to me is the best part of small business).

The seasonal flavors are always fun and creative, my current favorite is the Pumpkin Chai Latte (with a shot of espresso )! My mood instantly changes for the better after my first sip of Alice Jules every time!

The coffee is amazing to take home too (I love the Charlie Brown roast for my homemade cold brew!).

This is my happy place!!!
Visiting from out of town. Very charming   local owned business
I absolutely  LOVE  Alice Jules!! The coffee is fabulous and the welcoming atmosphere as well as the sweet helpful baristas make it a must stop!
This is the best coffee I've ever tasted! Worth an hour drive to get one every time! A seriously cute little jewelry selection too. Interesting.
A whole vibe. Love it

We were heading to SC and decided to check out this coffee house.  Omg, this coffee shop is adorable!  The owner greeted us when I was taking pictures and walking in!  He was very friendly and welcoming!

As I walked in, I was amazed with all of the Halloween and Fall decorations.  I felt like a little kid!  Kyle welcomed us, with a great big smile, when we got to the counter.  He was very friendly, helpful,  knowledgeable and awesome!  I loved his energy and vibe!  He helped me figure out what to order.  Jordyn made our drinks which were DELICIOUS!!!   She was so sweet,  friendly and helpful!

I ordered a 16 oz hot Cousin Itt - salted caramel and white chocolate!  My daughter ordered a 12 oz iced Matcha Latte.   The only problem with the drinks were that we chose the wrong cup size as our drinks were out of this world delicious!!  Next time we will definitely get the 20 oz!!!  If I could give more than 5 stars, I definitely would!!!

We are so thankful to have this sweet little coffee shop in our town! The owners and their son in law are genuinely welcoming, the variety of coffees and teas are superb, and the atmosphere is perfectly relaxing :)

Kent and his staff are wonderful.  The coffee and pastries are delicious.  Alice Jules is such a great place to spend a hour, do a little work on your computer, and enjoy a slow start to your morning.
The best service, in the neatest place, with the sweetest people. Truly a treasure! I would ALWAYS recommend Alice Jules.

The cutest local coffee shop in downtown Monroe!! Best owners and delicious drinks and treats. 10/10 Great places to sit indoor or outdoors!! Has gluten free treats, usually one really great one thats also dairy free, and has many dairy free and vegan drink options.
There's no place better than Alice Jules!!  The owner and staff are amazing and friendly.  Love going there to hang out!

love, love, LOVE alice jules! i've never been to a coffee shop like it before. i've been going here for years now and have never had one single complaint. the service is always fantastic, the atmosphere of the shop is absolutely beautiful (i'm not a huge fan of this modern, all-white look that places are trying to do nowadays) and is so incredibly comfortable. it's truly a gem in monroe and there's nothing like it. i always get an iced dirty chai with oat milk when i go out for coffee, and alice jules is the only place that consistently makes an amazing chai. the owners are also so kind and so welcoming, i've never been there at the same time that kent has been there without him greeting me and having a conversation with me and my friends. if i could give more than 5 stars, i absolutely would.
This is my favorite coffee shop in greater Charlotte. Plain latte, extra hot, every time.
Great coffee shop in Monroe with sweet treats!!

Alice Jules Coffeehouse is a true gem in Monroe. Their coffee is consistently outstanding and has me coming back for more. The warm and inviting atmosphere is matched by a team that is always friendly and welcoming. Beyond their exceptional coffee, we deeply appreciate Alice Jules for their unwavering support of our nonprofit, Council on Aging in Union County. Their commitment to the community shines through in everything they do. Alice Jules Coffeehouse is more than just a coffee shop; it's a place where our community comes together.
Alice Jules provides more than just a great cup of coffee. Its owners and staff are invariably friendly and welcoming. They can brighten your day and pick you up before the caffeine kicks in.

Easily the best coffee shop in downtown Monroe. From the great coffee, to fantastic employees - it's my favorite place to enjoy on my day off. They have something for everyone, and a menu of endless possibilities. The baristas always greet you with a smile, and will treat you like family. I definitely feel like the coffee is brewed especially for me (because sometimes it is, you seriously need to try the toasted marshmallow iced coffee.)
It has the nicest owners, the kindest couple in Monroe some say. They're always contributing and supporting the community, and making everyone feel welcome. To me, Alice Jules is the heart of my small town - and I hope you feel that way when you visit too!
What can I say about this place? The staff is outstanding

I love coming here each weekend! The staff is friendly and personable. I change my order every time, yet they still know before I order what I'm leaning toward. I especially love the mornings the fellow Swiftie girls are working and have Taylor playing in the background while they sing along. I highly recommend every cold brew flavor and the spinach and pesto pastry!
My daughter is a Wingate student and I was down to visit and we popped in to your lovely coffee shop!  Our lattes were delicious and our cake roll treats were great!!
Our favorite coffee house! Great coffee, great treats and the best staff!! We love Alice Jules!
Love Alice Jules! The Chilly Alices are amazing not to mention the atmosphere and the friendly staff.

Such a great place!!
And consistently great!!!!!!
Best coffee in town and delightful treats.
Friendly staff and helpful.
Such a lovely place with the kindest people! We love getting out coffee from there and enjoy the kind and knowledgeable locals and the atmosphere of Alice Jules!
Great little coffee shop. Good place to study or work. Headphones recommended!
Fantastic local coffee shop! The Jamaican Me Crazy and Capt. Jack's Java are amazing black. I always try to stop by every time I'm in Monroe.
He was closing, but stopped what he was doing too make me some much needed coffee.  Great customer service and even better coffee.  Truly love this place!
Very accommodating in friendly owners. We'll definitely come here again when in town.
Dope Coffee!

I love this place so much! It is very cozy and welcoming. The staff are very friendly and I absolutely love their gluten free pastry options and macaroons! Absolutely delicious. I'm not much of a coffee drinker myself; but my husband loves the coffee and I enjoy the cheer wine. :)
Best coffee! And ya Gotta go there on Thursdays! It's Capitan Jack Day is the best!
All the staff are very friendly and welcoming Alice Jules is one of my favorite places to be
Love this coffee shop! Staff is great! And you may get a song or two sung for you! What a delight!
Great coffee and stuffed bagels.
Cozy place with seating inside and outside.

This has been a long time study spot for me and my classmates. I absolutely love the atmosphere, the ambience, and the snacks/drinks! I recommend it to everyone looking for a place to chill, study, or hang out with friends. Love love love AJ's!

This place is such a gem of a spot - great place to study and enjoy a coffee with a friend. I've taken so many ppl here when they come to visit and they all love it!! Thank you to the wonderful staff for always making us feel welcome!!
I love coming to Alice Jules, they always treat you like you are family and have the best coffee drinks in Union County.
The absolute BEST coffee house hands down! Friendly and caring owners and staff! I'm a daily customer

Props to Kyle (the cashier) and Jordyn (the barista) for making today a special day! My wife and I have a coffee date every Saturday, visiting local coffee shops. This one is one of the BEST! It has a hometown vibe, local art on the walls, and the coffee is always excellent! (Kent, the owner, is pretty cool, too!)

There is just no better place for coffee in downtown Monroe! Kent, the owner, and his staff are absolutely the most wonderful people and make everyone feel like family! If you haven't tried them you need to take the time to make a trip there.
Absolute best coffee in town.   We love this Downtown Monroe staple. Best staff, best coffee and BEST OWNER!
How could you not LOVE this place!!!   Best coffee in town.  Love the owner and staff.  They are truly my favorite for all COFFEE!
Great coffee, tasty cake roll, an alright atmosphere. Quite busy at brunch time.
The smoothies are so good. I also recommend their scones.
Smooth tasting coffee, and danish was fresh and delicious
Awesome!

My favorite coffee shop in Monroe! I make sure to visit every time I'm in town. The baristas are always friendly and quick. I love looking at the jewelry and crotchet items they have for sale. I've always loved their lattes but recently tried their chilly Alice and it is incredible. I love how you can taste the espresso. It's a perfect drink for the summer. Highly recommend!

Coffee/espresso: phenomenal & consistent, high quality!
Service: so sweet, I feel like I'm brought into the community even though I'm just visiting.
Atmosphere: so perfect for what they're going for.

I've had a really rough week and the employees really brightened my day.

I remember coming here years ago when I was in high school and it was great then, but it's even better now. Thank you for a beautiful coffee shop experience, y'all are amazing.

Alice Jules has great coffee and amazing service from a super friendly staff. The owner is one of the nicest people you'll ever meet, and he cultivates that mindset with his staff.

The coffee is excellent, and they partner with multiple other local businesses to provide fresh pastries and muffins as well.

The building has several great spaces to sit and chat or to get some work done. If you show up during a peak time, though, it can be challenging to find a parking space. There is a large public parking space a couple blocks away, though, so it's never a huge issue.

Overall, this is one of my favorite coffee spots anywhere.

Great service. The baristas are quick, considerate, and know what they're doing and talking about. Nice, quaint location. It is local, affordable and just on the outskirts of the city, so near a number of shops, but not crowded by traffic. Would totally recommend giving it a try.

What a great experience!! My husband and I got a dark hot chocolate and white hot chocolate, respectively, and our friends got coffee drinks. Everything was delicious and smooth. Best of all, the people who work here are AWESOME. They greet you with genuine warmth, and you feel like you're being served by friends. They are knowledgeable about the menu, provide quick service, and made us feel so welcome. We'll be back!
Great experience. The staff was SO friendly; Michelle, Jordan, and the owner key. Such a cool place too.
Super sweet owners and staff. Wonderful coffee. Great atmosphere
First time visiting Alice Jules, and I'll be coming back! What a great time meeting Kent, sipping coffee, and spending a Monroe morning with family! Alice Jules feels like home!
Tasty, quick, cheap, and a great service!
People and atmosphere is fantastic and super nice.  Coffee is great.  The baked goods are ok could be better.  Parking is often not enough.
I go here multiple times a week and have never been disappointed. The coffee, pastries, and the staff are all wonderful. Highly recommend to anyone nearby.
Love this gem of a coffee social house
I love going here!! Everyone is so nice and the atmosphere is cozy!
Great coffee
Small local shop.  Excellent hot coffee and teas. Small assortment of bagels, muffins, and sweets.  Now has no sugar chai tea. Yummy.
Beautiful house, the pictures sold me on visiting.  Ordered a Lavender latte and it was  very disappointing.  It made gas station coffee seem complex and rich.
Lovely place and lovely people.  We recommend this sweet place.

What an amazing place with amazing people! I stopped in to buy a dessert. I'm not a coffee fan! Kyle was working and told me he could make me something he knows I would like! I doubted him, but obliged. He made me something called Santa's Milk and Cookies Chi. It was the most delicious hot drink I've ever had! I was very pleasantly surprised! Michelle was working too. She showed me the favorites board and told me to try the Apple Pie Chi next time. I definitely will do so! This place will be a new frequent stop for me! Thank you Kyle and Michelle for getting me hooked on trying new drinks! BTW, they have great desserts!
Best coffee around, great location with nice seating areas inside and outside, and staff are very friendly!
Tiny sitting area but great coffee and people.
Nice place to have a quality coffee product
The best coffee ever. Highly recommended.

This is coffee shop stop number 20 for us and it did not disappoint!  It's a beautiful converted home that has the best vibe around.  The coffee was amazing and the food was excellent.  Santa happened to be there as well which was an added bonus!  The staff were amazing and working hard.  We happened to show up at a really busy time but there was no delay in our order.  Highly recommend this place for the coffee and atmosphere!
Love Alice Jules! Excellent service, excellent coffee, and excellent whole beans for purchase!
Comfortable coffee shop with a great variety of beans to take to go! Service has been great too.

What an amazing place!! we found this little place when there for a quick visit from MI and have known Melody and Kent ever since. They are just the kindest people AND the coffee, food and atmosphere are amazing! We have been ordering from them for the past 4 years and the quality stays high and getting to talk to the people is always like a warm welcome home!! I also bought the best earrings and necklace there and love that they support local artists and the community.  If you are in town please stop by, you are in for a real treat!

Had an awesome first time popping in here with my toddler for a morning coffee and pastry. Service was super quick, coffee and the muffin we chose were delicious, and the staff was beyond welcoming, friendly, and on top of their game. The sitting area was spacious and lovely; nice calm atmosphere with beautiful local artwork displayed. Highly recommend, we will HAVE to return!

We recently moved to NC and had to leave our home coffee shop. I'm so glad we found Alice Jules because now we have a new coffee home!
Their coffee is amazing and the atmosphere is perfect. Everyone is so friendly and they have some great events for the family also.
If you live nearby or are just driving through, Alice Jules is a place you must stop at and a Monroe staple.

I needed a quiet space to do some work so I found this place on Google.  When I walked in, I was instantly greeted by the sweet staff.  I didn't know what I wanted but knew it needed to be apple, the staff recommended the Apple Chai.  I'd never had chai before but let me tell you... It was amazing.  I found a spot in the dining room in a corner to work.  I stayed for about an hour and a half plugging away.  The atmosphere was amazing and probably the best coffee shop atmosphere I've ever been to.  I'm so grateful for this sweet family owned business.  I didn't grow up here (came here through my husbands job) but I'm SO THANKFUL for small businesses like this that treat their customers like family.  Every person that came in was greeted and honestly the guy knew them by name.  People are repeat customers because of the customer service and quality of products offered.  Thank you for making my drink today and letting me hang out for a little bit! <3
We just had cold brew coffee. It was ok.
Fantastic food and drinks, very friendly service. The whole experience is very warm and welcoming. A great place to meet friends or come by yourself and study, work, or read.

I ordered a new drink I was unfamiliar with and did not like it as much as I thought I would (no fault of the shop). I asked them to doctor it slightly but they went above and beyond to make me a completely different drink without me really asking (They insisted!) Very friendly staff! Super nice atmosphere - lovely outdoor area. Kyle and Kent were exceptionally kind and helpful!
This place never disappoints!!

Very friendly staff & helpful for someone like me who isn't a fan of the coffee flavor but likes the iced and blended flavor types.  Sometimes I'm not sure what I want but know what I don't like. I'm appreciative when the person taking my order is understanding and helpful. For this great 1st experience today, I definitely plan to return.
(I forget the name of my drink, but it's a blended creme brule....mix of the caramel & vanilla since I was torn about which of the two flavors I preferred.  See what I mean? Excellent, knowledgeable, helpful & even insightful).
Good people, making good coffee. Positive, easy going staff. Hope their business continues to prosper for their great efforts.

My wife and I love Alice Jules! Staff is always the friendliest and welcoming and the coffee is great.

We love the iced vanilla latte with and extra shot of espresso.

A great little coffee shop in Downton Munroe. My only complaint is they serve everything in disposable containers.
Come on USA let's produce less waste.
cute spot with pretty good coffee

Visiting from Syracuse, NY and I have to say this coffee house was so cozy and welcoming. The owner is very generous as well as the staff. I had gone 3 days in a row with my friend. The cold brew Jamaican Me Crazy was insanely delicious. It has a cool antique shop attached as well. A variety of small breakfast goods and trinkets available too! Highly recommend to all
This is my go to for coffee and snacks. Everything is delicious and the service is impeccable. The building is very quaint and cozy. It's a great place to meet friends at and chat for a while.
Love Alice Jules!  The staff has the best customer service in town!

Owner is friendly and accommodating. It was busy but they work fast. We had sticky buns which he heated for us. Yummy. You can purchase whole coffee beans too. Seating inside or outside on porch. Very cozy. You feel like a part of the family there. I'm sure we'll return.
Great as always. Nothing more to add :)
My latte was perfectly balanced here. We also shared a cinnamon bun muffin and it was sensational. I'm definitely coming back!
My iced chai latte was fabulous, and the baristas (and owner) are super friendly! It's a great atmosphere filled with a variety of local artisan creations.

My husband, sister & I walked with our 2 dogs to Alice Jules the past couple mornings & we are so happy that we have discovered this coffee shop.

I love that they support other local businesses by selling those businesses pastries. I don't go into a coffee shop expecting an iced spiced chai to be anything super special, but it's delicious here! If you're used to spending Starbucks money, then you will be shocked by how much more affordable this place is.

Most of all, I think that Kyle is an awesome person! While waiting for my drink to be made, I noticed how they recognized nearly everyone who came in & remembered their usual orders. They made sure that our dogs had clean water in the provided dog bowl on the patio. It was obvious that they genuinely cares about everyone having a good experience. I hope Kyle gets some employee appreciation for all of their efforts!
Ran in to get a pound of ground coffee. We love the Toasted Coconut. I grabbed a cold dirty Chai to go, my favorite.
Can't get enough of Alice Jules!
We enjoy the great customer service and excellent quality of coffee.
The best coffee house ever! Love the people, the drinks, the beans, and the convenience of the location!!
Alice Jules has delicious coffees and pasties. Everyone that works there has been so very nice! I definitely recommend stopping by.

Just came for the first time and loved the shop! Friendly staff, clean shop, quick service. The Mr. Darcy coffee (iced) was delicious! Very cute atmosphere, with plenty of seating thoughtfully arranged with lots of nooks - it was perfect for a catch up with friends! We had a great little space to talk without feeling like we were disturbing anyone else, or being interrupted by other conversations. Big props to the owners!
Great coffee and setting!
I'm the nephew of the owner and I love working and all the fun drinks they have.

A little piece of heaven on earth! I love starting my day here at Alice Jules...whether I'm sitting on the porch enjoying my tea and a book, or sitting in the parlor visiting with friends I always feel welcome! Georgia, Kyle, Jordyn and Caitlin always greet us with a smile and their attentiveness to details is spot on!! It's definitely a gem among gems in downtown Monroe!
Don't miss an opportunity to stop in and say hey and grab a coffee, tea, smoothie or chilly Alice...

Looking for good coffee? Look no further!!! You will NEVER find a coffee shop that  feels more like home!! Each and every wonderful person working there are not only the best baristas in Union county, they're also the kindest people that I like to call my friends! They're all such a blessing and always leave me with a huge smile on my face!

A local gem. We love Kent and all the baristas at Alice Jules! Everyone is so friendly and the drinks are always great. I do have my go-to drink, but if I'm in the mood for something different, they always help me by concocting something fun and just right. Stopping by for our favorite morning drinks has become a weekend ritual for my husband and I and our dog Wally -- getting his pup cup is a MUST, and Kent always makes sure he gets it! Alice Jules Crew, as always, we appreciate your presence in Monroe and your hospitality, warmth, small-town charm, and great drinks!
The owner was super nice and genuine. He really made me feel cared about and valued as a customer. Also, the creme brulee latte was delicious!
They have the best coffee! I'm currently breastfeeding can only drink decaf, their captain jack decaf is the best if you like cinnamon.
LOVE this place!! Check it out! You will love it too.
Great coffee and very friendly service! Got a bagel bomb and it was delicious. I've gotten numerous coffee drinks there and they have all been great.

We are new to Monroe and we just love this little coffee shop we found! The drinks are great as are the pastries and the staff and owner are wonderful as well. It encompasses everything I love about a small town. We highly recommend this place!

Update: another daughter mom date today! Enjoyed it all minus gluten free offerings. which they don't bake so not directly at fault but they always leave me sick to my stomach for some reason. Maybe a sweetener.

The bulk of my four stars for Alice Jewels is because of the environment. I love going to sit here and work or read, and wish I could get down to them more often. My daughter and I go sit here when I take my son to his art class nearby, and we always have a great time.

My four stars instead of five is because the coffee is not my personal favorite. The beans are great but something about how the shots are pulled is a little off for me. Never stopped me from going though. Miles ahead of Starbucks and other chains and your latte won't break the bank. (Did I mention that the deck layout is perfect for Dino romping? I have it on good authority).
Adorable little coffee shop inside of part of an old Victorian house (the other part is an antiques shop).  Quaint and truly TONS of coffee flavor options!  WiFi is not that strong but the coffee is!
First time here, and it was great. Coffee, service and atmosphere all great
Stopped in for coffee while in town for an event. Coffee was great! Seemed very popular with the locals.
Delicious Dirty Chai lattes hot or cold!
Wonderful place!
Great coffee, food, and people.

Yummy coffee and scones in a Victorian setting!
What a nice place!

I have had the opportunity to try out a handful of coffee shops in the Charlotte and surrounding areas and I can say that Alice Jules is the friendliest, most welcoming spot I have been to! The coffee is also DELICIOUS!!! You walk in with a friendly hello and get to enjoy a historical home that has been transformed into the coffee shop! Highly recommended!!! They even did a drawing while I was there to give away a free bag of coffee! So sweet!!
It was the best americano I've ever had!
Super cute antique style coffeehouse with friendly staff! My Americano was pretty weak for a coffee shop so next time I'll ask for a double shot, but the scone was delicious!

This is one of my favorite places for coffee! The kids like their Italian sodas (like the ones they used to have at Barnes and Noble) and they have a lot of good latte options. If you don't love super sweet coffee, just ask them to go light in their syrups!! The kids also love that the owner sometimes gives them an Oreo when he's there working!
Love this little coffee shop! They cater to the customer and I've NEVER had a bad cup of coffee. You really do become family here and I constantly brag to friends and family about this little spot!
I bought the winter seasonal drink, the one that has white chocolate and cinnamon. It was reasonably priced for a large cup of 20 Oz.
Great cozy place to relax

Best service around. The owner saw me holding my treats and came from around the counter with a bag for me and held it open so I could put my treats in. He also came outside to bring us plates and let us know there were tables open inside. I've been to other coffee houses where I was ignored he made us feel like he knew us!! Husband loved his white chocolate mocha and I enjoyed my iced coffee and our muffin and cookie bar.
Great coffee shop near downtown Monroe. Very historic building- lo eved the atmosphere. The Peppermint Patty frozen was super yummy. My 11 year old loved his cookie and hot chocolate.
Cute and adorable coffee shop..nice place to unwind... delicious coffee and tasty treats
Great coffee and great atmosphere
Lovely cozy little coffee shop with great coffee and great people. Inside and outside seating. Traditional coffee shop foods available and some local jewelry.
Absolutely a delightful coffeehouse!!!! A must visit! Staff members are very friendly, knowledgeable and helpful. I will be back
Super cute and festive for Halloween! The pastries were fresh and delicious, and the coffee was strong and flavorful. Fast and friendly service.
Such a great environment to work and meet up with people! The staff really developed a welcoming environment! I recommend you try the favorite drinks from the Baristas, specially Logan's!

Went to Alice Jules for the first date I had with my amazing girlfriend, had such a lovely time and have been back several times since! Very friendly management and staff and a lovely antique shop on the side! What a wonderful spot, filled with wonderful memories for me!
Great little coffee shop in downtown Monroe. Hometown friendly staff
Any time we can~ Alice Jules is definitely our go to. Delicious drinks and AWESOME customer service every time!!
Great service. The manager is the sweetest. Love this place.
Great atmosphere and coffee!
Tried the Capt. Jack Java and it taste wonderful :) Thank you Alice Jules

I absolutely love the owner Ken he is so nice and treats my boys like his own. I swear I feel so welcome when I get coffee here my boys can be a bit loud and rowdy but, they understand that . The staff is amazing to us and the coffee taste incredible .I totally recommend every flavor on the menu considering I have tried every Chilly Alice there is to try. If your looking for a good coffee that's cold and sweet this summer Go get you one. They always have the best bakery items too.

From the moment we walked in we were greeted by the nicest most Genuine people! My pup got a puppuccino and my latte was SPECTACULAR!
Lovely place, wonderful atmosphere and delicious coffee! GO THERE!
Good, friendly service; very cozy, homey feel to the sitting area; and good coffee and edible treats. I definitely recommend!

The creme Brule iced coffee was delicious. Had to make a special run out for a second coffee the next day since it was so good. There was different staff each day and they were both very nice and caring about their customers needs. Support this local business anytime u can. They were great. Thank you for an awesome experience.
Such great people and very good drinks!  110% recommend!
Love getting coffee here it's always so good! Great place and wonderful people!
Great local coffee shop!
We liked it and the service was great
I dont normally get coffee ever, because I usually have to fight through the tastes. The Carmella delight I got was freaking perfect right out the first sip though! So yea, that shop rocks.
Excellent coffee and a great place to sit and talk or relax. They have antiques there as well.
I go there all the time. Love it! One of my favorite places to just study and work on homework. They have great coffee and awesome staff.
A great place to relax and have an awesome cup of coffee.  The staff is so friendly!  Highly recommend
Good coffee. Cute place.
Such a cute coffee shop with a relaxed environment! Staff was friendly and helpful. I will definitely be back for their white mocha!
Absolutely wonderful service. I was unsure of what I should get and was having a rough day. The woman who served me was patient, answered my questions, and made me feel cared for.
This place makes an excellent latte. Set in an old two story house in the historical district of Monroe. A hidden gem.
Great atmosphere, old town charm. Latte was great.
This was my first visit and man I have been missing out. The decor is superb, the coffee taste fantastic, and customer service was top notch. This is my new spot for sure.
Cute shop, lots of seating indoors and out, some pastries for sale.
Everyone was SO very friendly!!  Coffee and pastries are delicious!
Great coffee, my favorite is an iced honey cinnamon latte. A nice display of artwork that is available for purchase.
its a house
Amazing drinks in a very beautiful Victorian House.
Kent and Melody do an exceptional job of making everyone feel like family.

I apologize for the 3 star review before. That was a mistake on my behalf . Myself and girlfriend was in & out really quickly on the 17th of Nov. As we was leaving thought she had the bag and she thought I had it. About an hour and half later realized how crazy we probably looked and rushed back. It had insulin, I needed inside and was very important it was still inside bag when I returned for it. Your staff was very nice and I really appreciate the way they secured my bag and safely held it until my return. They handled the situation very kindly and unjudgemental as well.So please accept my deepest apologies for the 3 star rating before I didn't realize I had even given one. So please accept  the rating you and your staff deserve. I  give you guys 5  Oh, one last thing my girlfriend said the sweet tea was amazing
Wonderful coffee
Good coffee and I got myself an early  Christmas present
I go there almost every day. Everyone is friendly.
Always friendly and wonderful coffee and service

First stop at this coffee shop while driving though town was a great find. Kent and his staff are so friendly and I appreciated the positivity and faith based notes sprinkled throughout his establishment. Best chai tea latte and pumpkin strudel muffin I've ever had. Enjoyed some Bible reading outdoors on the beautiful porch. However, watch out for local politicians beating your ear about unsolicited information, to try to earn a vote, even after you explain you're not a resident...
Good selection of sweet treats with your coffee. Friendly people! :)

I am so in love with this place. We were taking a drive from Charlotte with no destination. We drove by the cutest coffee shop with antique store next door. We had to stop and have some coffee. When I say cutest, I mean like Gilmore Girls set cute!

The place was all decorated with pumpkins and Halloween crafts. I mean they even had a Cousin Itt! Cousin Itt has never looked this good!

As for the owner and baristas? They were the kindest. Even though they were closing, they chased us down and offered us some coffee anyway. We sat outside on the patio and just had the best time.

I 100% recommend stopping by and will no doubt drive 30+ minutes to experience this again.
Very nice people. Feels like home
Best. Coffee. Ever.
Love coming here to study. Very friendly staff and great coffee. I need to try some of their treats too

What a marvellous place. Yeah, tons of bland chain coffee shops off the highway, but then you'd miss out on how awesome this place is.

I've never tasted a pumpkin coffee that tasted like anything other than flavoured syrup, but they managed to make one that tastes like actual pumpkin pie in coffee form. Compete with pumpkin whipped cream.

So glad I stopped by on my way through town.
Great coffee, friendly staff, and great atmosphere!
Excellent coffee! Friendly staff and delicious deserts too :)
Super friendly, family oriented coffee shop. Amazing coffee and delicious pastries!
Definitely the best coffee shop in Monroe. Friendly and fast service every time. The shop is a cute little place inside an old house. Lots of great pastries and the coffee is amazing. Great spot
Friendly environment with great tasting coffee, better than Starbucks. support local businesses.

This was my first time to Alice Jules.  I found the staff welcoming and knowledgeable.  They have a good selection of coffees. I got a large Costa Rica which was pre made.  I braced for the usual Luke warm and over extracted liquid I usually find.  This was pleasantly hot and perfectly extracted.  The tasting notes were there and well balanced. No outstanding bitterness and it was hot without being too hot.  This coffee was as close to a perfect cup as possible.  The shop's layout and ambiance was pleasant also.  I plan to make this place my go to coffee shop until I get my roaster back up.
Great coffee house and wonderful service
Great people love the atmosphere and decor. Just an awesome vibe to start your day off.
The best coffee in Monroe!  Everyone is so friendly.
Cute place great service!
Cozy coffee house with a variety of pastries to choose from
Super friendly staff, small town feel, great espresso. What more could you ask for? I go every time I'm in town.

What a cute coffee shop! My daughter and I stopped in this morning and got muffins and beverages, and we enjoyed it so much!! They make Italian Soda like we used to get back home at our old church (we haven't found it anywhere else down here) and my cafe au lait was perfect! We'll definitely be returning
Super-good coffee, and super-friendly staff!!!

Happy to add my 5 star review to all the many others!! Fantastic coffee shop and now our favorite " happy place" to get a perfect brew and sit and chill.  Very clean and well run, plus friendly owner and staff. Highly recommend!

My wife and I have been here many times and have never had anything we didn't like. Coffees and hot chocolates are excellent and the customer service is great. When the owner is working, he goes out of his way to check on you and make sure you are happy. We have never had anything we didn't like, but I would bet if something were not acceptable and you were to tell him, he would bend over backwards to make it right. Nice quaint shop with interesting artwork.
A nice little diversion from the big coffee chains!
Excellent customer service! Always very welcoming. Charming small coffeehouse right downtown in Monroe. Worth every penny!
Met the people there for the first time this morning, nice, friendly, but please be careful, the coffee is extremely hot !!! I had the blueberry, it was awesome !!!
